# Wedding planning app — design system v2
## Direction: "Modern romantic" (the approved mockup is the reference)

A calm, fast tool with restrained romance. Whitespace and precise type carry it; serif and
plum appear only at emotional moments; couple surfaces breathe, planner surfaces tighten.
The approved mockup at `design/reference.html` is the canonical visual spec — match it for
exact sizing, spacing, and component structure.

Tokens and fonts are fixed (see bottom). Don't change them.

---

## Type scale (bold, high-contrast)

The look comes from contrast: huge display moments against small, quiet UI. Don't make
everything bigger — make the hero bigger and keep the chrome tight.

Display (Cormorant Garamond 600, emotional moments only)
- Couple-names hero: `clamp(40px, 6vw, 54px)` — can push toward 64px for more drama
- Countdown number: 64px, color plum
- Planner slim-hero names: 26px

UI (Hanken Grotesk, 400/500)
- Panel/section title: 20px / 500 · Stat number: 26px / 500 · Budget figure: 22px / 500
- Body & rows: 15–16px · Table cells: 14px · Captions/meta: 12–13px
- Eyebrow label: 12px / 500, letter-spacing 0.06em, sentence case

One or two big serif moments per screen (hero, countdown); everything else small sans.
The gap between them is the design.

---

## Component inventory (exact CSS lives in design/reference.html)

- Topbar: porcelain, 1px stone bottom border, wordmark with 7px plum dot, nav pill links
  (active = plum-deep on plum-tint), segmented Couple/Planner toggle (active = plum/white).
- Pill/status: 12px, dot + label; variants default, sage, clay, rosewood, plum.
- Button: radius 12, 9/18 padding; primary = plum/white, hover plum-deep; secondary =
  surface + stone border.
- Card: surface bg, 1px stone border, radius-lg (16).
- WeddingHero (signature): centered names (display, clamp 40–54) + date (sans muted) +
  64px plum countdown + label, hairline rule beneath, gentle rise-in (respect reduced-motion).
- Timeline: vertical 1px stone spine, nodes (done = sage, current = plum + plum-tint ring),
  tasks as quiet rows with pills.
- Vendor stepper: dot + label + connector; lit steps in plum.
- Budget: figure + progress bar (stone track, plum fill) + line items (tabular-nums).
- Planner: slim-hero strip, 3 stat cards, planner-grid (260px couples rail + dense outreach
  table; right-aligned tabular Quote column).

---

## Layout & density
- Couple: single column, max-width 760px, padding 56px 24px 96px, generous rhythm.
- Planner: max-width 1180px, compact rows, slim hero, 260px rail + table grid.
- Hairline stone separators + whitespace, not heavy gray cards.
- :focus-visible = 2px plum outline. Honor prefers-reduced-motion.

---

## Hard don'ts (these keep it off the generic look)
- No script fonts, floral graphics, gold gradients, or blush-pink floods.
- Serif ONLY for hero/countdown and >=28px emotional moments — never UI chrome.
- Plum is an accent, never a background flood.
- Flat only: no gradients, heavy shadows, glow. Two sans weights (400/500).

---

## Tokens (fixed)
